    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 2, 3: Confocal imaging of cultured hippocampal neurons showed over-expression of IQGAP1 stimulated spine formation and increased spine head size. The effect was strongly reduced in an IQGAP1 mutant lacking the CHD domain.\n\nFigure 5: IQGAP1 mutants that lacks C-terminus also stimulates spine formation; deletion of this domain does not prevent the stimulatory effect of IQGAP1 on spine number or spine head size.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Embryonic day-18 rat embryos (euthanized by CO2 overdose) were used to prepare primary hippocampal cultures as previously described [35]-[40].\"\n\n\"For IQGAP1-sh\nForward: 5'TGCCATGGATGAGATTGGAAAGCTTTCCAATCTCATCCATGGCACTTTTTTG and.\nReverse: 5'AATTCAAAAAGTGCCATGGATGAGATTGGAAAGCTTTCCAATCTCATCCATGGCA.\"",
